<plot>After their evening show is over, Henry King and his orchestra members visit an ice-skating rink, and discover that ice-skating is harder than it looks. Little Shirley Foster, the skating child-wonder, appears and goes through her graceful routines. This gives King an idea for a skating-carnival night club starring little Miss Mason, and,of course, the Henry King Orchestra.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?423283</url></doc>
